Audience ID.description: ID of the Audience that received Impressions.

Audience Name.description: Name of the Audience that received Impressions.

Audience Type.description: Type of the Audience that received Impressions [General Interest Category/Custom Audience/Custom Segment].

Audience Status.description: Status of the Audience that received Impressions (ON, OFF).

Gender.description: The gender of the user: F, M, or U.

Device Type.description: Device type of the user: Desktop, Tablet, Phone, Unknown.

DMA WOEID.description: The Where on Earth ID associated with the DMA.

City WOEID.description: The Where on Earth ID associated with the City.

State WOEID.description: The Where on Earth ID associated with the State.

Zip WOEID.description: The Where on Earth ID associated with the Zip Code.

Country WOEID.description: The Where on Earth ID associated with the Country.

Location Type.description: Flags whether the location listed in the report indicates the physical location of the user or the location of their intent (for Search).

Post Click Conversions.description: The total number of post click conversions.

Post Impression Conversions.description: The total number of post view conversions.

Conversions.description: The total number of conversions, which includes both post click and post view conversions. For app install campaigns, the default conversion windows are 7 days post-click and 1 day post view. For website conversions, the default windows are 30 days post-click and 2 days post-view.

Total Conversions.description: A synonym for the Conversions field (maintained for backwards compatibility).

Spend.description: The unadjusted spend amount. Note that adjustments - meaning any corrections due to issues like overcharging - can be queried using the adjustment_stats cube.

Reblog Rate.description: The rate of Tumblr Reblogs (over Impressions).

Follow Rate.description: The rate of Tumblr Follows (over Impressions).

Engagements.description: The count of total Tumblr Engagements.

Engagement Rate.description: The rate of total Tumblr Engagements (over Impressions).

Paid Engagement Rate.description: The rate of revenue-bearing Engagements (over Impressions).

Video 25% Complete.description: The number of times the video played to 25% of its length.

Video 50% Complete.description: The number of times the video played to 50% of its length.

Video 75% Complete.description: The number of times the video played to 75% of its length.

Video 100% Complete.description: The number of times the video played to 100% of its length.

Cost Per Video View.description: The average cost per video view.

Video Closed.description: The number of times the video was closed.

Video Skipped.description: The number of times the video was skipped.

Video after 30 seconds view.description: The number of times the video played longer than 30 seconds.

Ad Extn Impressions.description: Total impressions for which an ad extension was displayed.

Ad Extn Clicks.description: Total clicks on an ad extension link (rather than the main link).

Ad Extn Spend.description: Total spend associated to an ad extension.

Average Position.description: The average position of the ad.

Fact Conversion Counting.description: The way your conversions were counted for the campaign during the report time range (ALL_PER_INTERACTION, ONE_PER_INTERACTION).
